This is alpha release 0.206 of Term::Size::Win32.

Term::Size::Win32 is a Perl module which provides a straightforward 
way to get the size of the Win32 terminal (or window) on which 
a script is running.

NOTE: This distribution was made to install even in non-Win32
systems. It is done by skipping all tests if Win32::Console
is not installed. But it is not going to work in these cases.
